---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Investors & Partners — PEPHORMIA" description="A live, compliant peptide & hormone business opening a small private partnership round.">
<div class="wrap">
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="eyebrow">INVESTORS & PARTNERS / SYS.05</div>
    <h1>Back the only brand that grades the science and sells the products.</h1>
    <p class="sub">PEPHORMIA is a live, compliant peptide &amp; hormone business with three revenue streams. We're opening
      a small partnership round — a handful of aligned partners who grow with it. This page is the story; the terms are
      shared privately on request.</p>
  </section>

  <div class="kpis">
    <div class="kpi"><div class="n"><span>3</span> streams</div><div class="l">Topicals · Digital · Print — one trusted core</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="n"><span>25%</span> total</div><div class="l">Offered across all partners — max 3 partners</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="n"><span>2003</span></div><div class="l">ABN active since — a 20+ yr registered AU business</div></div>
    <div class="kpi"><div class="n">Live</div><div class="l">Site, brand, product & content library shipped</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- MOAT -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="eyebrow">THE MOAT</div>
    <h2>Why us — and why no one else does this</h2>
    <div class="moat">
      <h3>Nobody combines graded, cited education with commerce across topicals + digital + print.</h3>
      <p>The evidence-grading platforms (like Examine) grade the science but <span class="hl">sell no product</span>.
        The skincare brands (The Ordinary, NIOD) sell product but <span class="hl">grade no evidence</span> — they
        reach for claims. PEPHORMIA does both: every product sits on top of honestly-graded, cited research, and the
        same trusted core powers cosmetics, digital guides and print. That combination is the moat — hard to fake,
        hard to copy, and exactly what a distrustful, overwhelmed audience is searching for.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- COMPETITOR TABLE -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="eyebrow">WHERE WE STAND</div>
    <h2>The landscape, honestly mapped</h2>
    <p class="lead">Real brands, real positioning. We sit at premium quality and fair price — and we're the only one
      spanning education, digital and print alongside the topical.</p>
    <table>
      <thead><tr>
        <th>Brand</th><th>Copper-peptide serum (typical)</th><th>Graded evidence</th><th>Digital guides</th><th>Print / POD</th><th>Position</th>
      </tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td class="brand">The Ordinary</td><td class="price-col">~A$40 / 30ml (1%)</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td>Budget commodity, claim-led</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="brand">NIOD</td><td class="price-col">~A$70–90 / 30ml (1%)</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td>Premium, science-styled</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="brand">Vitali</td><td class="price-col">~A$60+ (2–3%)</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td>High-strength, US premium</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="brand">Neurogan / ANAIRUI</td><td class="price-col">~A$16–30</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td class="no">—</td><td>Budget, volume</td></tr>
        <tr><td class="brand">Examine.com</td><td class="price-col">No products</td><td class="yes">Yes</td><td class="yes">Yes</td><td class="no">—</td><td>Evidence only, no commerce</td></tr>
        <tr class="us"><td class="brand">PEPHORMIA</td><td class="price-col">A$44 / 30ml (1%)</td><td class="yes">Yes</td><td class="yes">Yes</td><td class="yes">Yes</td><td>The only all-four combination</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <div class="why3" style="margin-top:20px">
      <div class="whyc"><div class="k">Quality</div><h3>Premium formula, fair price</h3><p>1% GHK-Cu at A$44 — NIOD quality positioning without the NIOD price, and above budget commodities on formulation and honesty.</p></div>
      <div class="whyc"><div class="k">Compliance</div><h3>Built to survive review</h3><p>Cosmetic-grade, INCI-named, appearance-only. No therapeutic claims — so products stay sellable and ads stay approvable where rivals get flagged.</p></div>
      <div class="whyc"><div class="k">Trust</div><h3>A 20+ year AU business</h3><p>Operated under an ABN active since 2003, GST-registered, ASIC-registered business name. Real, accountable, Australian.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- GROWTH ENGINE -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="eyebrow">HOW WE GET SALES</div>
    <h2>The growth engine — a weekly content flywheel</h2>
    <p class="lead">One trusted evidence core, repurposed across five channels every week. Each feeds the next; the
      newsletter is the owned asset everything converts into.</p>
    <div class="engine">
      <div class="node"><div class="step">01 · AUTHORITY</div><h4>LinkedIn</h4><p>Founder POV + graded science. Builds credibility and B2B / partner reach.</p></div>
      <div class="node"><div class="step">02 · COMMUNITY</div><h4>Reddit</h4><p>Short, honest human replies in niche subs. Trust and search-indexed depth.</p></div>
      <div class="node"><div class="step">03 · REACH</div><h4>TikTok / Shorts</h4><p>Daily AI short-form. Top-of-funnel hooks that test what converts, cheaply.</p></div>
      <div class="node"><div class="step">04 · SEO CORE</div><h4>Blog</h4><p>Cited cornerstone articles. The evergreen engine that compounds in search.</p></div>
      <div class="node"><div class="step">05 · OWN IT</div><h4>Newsletter</h4><p>Beehiiv list. Where readers become buyers — the asset we own outright.</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="cadence">
      <span class="mono">TYPICAL WEEK · REPURPOSED FROM ONE EVIDENCE CORE</span>
      <table>
        <tr><th>Channel</th><th>Cadence</th><th>Job</th></tr>
        <tr><td>TikTok / Reels / Shorts</td><td>Daily (AI-generated)</td><td>Discovery + hook testing</td></tr>
        <tr><td>LinkedIn</td><td>3× / week</td><td>Authority + partners</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Reddit</td><td>3–5× / week</td><td>Community trust + long-tail SEO</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Blog</td><td>1–2× / week</td><td>Cornerstone SEO</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Newsletter</td><td>Weekly</td><td>Nurture → sale</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- OFFER -->
  <section class="sec">
    <div class="eyebrow">THE PARTNERSHIP ROUND</div>
    <h2>A small, private round</h2>
    <p class="lead">Real equity, weekly transparency, a fair independent-valuer exit after six months. The binding
      terms live in a private brief — request it and we'll talk.</p>
    <div class="offer">
      <div class="side">
        <h3>Structure at a glance</h3>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Stake</span><span class="v">1% per A$1,000 invested</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Total offered</span><span class="v">Max 25% of the business</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Partners</span><span class="v">Maximum 3</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Minimum ticket</span><span class="v">5% (A$5,000)</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Return</span><span class="v">Growth in stake value</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Transparency</span><span class="v">Weekly meetings</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Exit</span><span class="v">Fair value, after 6 months</span></div>
        <div class="termline"><span class="k">Structure</span><span class="v">Pty Ltd — when we proceed</span></div>
      </div>
      <div class="side">
        <h3>Request the brief</h3>
        <p style="font-size:13px;color:var(--muted)">The full partnership MOU — terms, structure options and the growth
          plan — is shared privately with genuinely interested partners. It's a private offer, not a public solicitation.</p>
        <a class="cta" href="mailto:raj@artigellence.com?subject=PEPHORMIA%20Partnership%20Brief">Request the partnership brief →</a>
        <div class="gated">
          Private offer to a maximum of three partners. Not a public offer of securities and not an invitation to the
          general public. Investment carries risk, including loss of capital. Not financial or legal advice — seek your own.
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</div>
<style>

  .hero{padding:56px 0 8px}
  .hero h1{font-size:42px;max-width:18ch}
  .hero .sub{color:var(--muted);max-width:62ch;margin-top:16px;font-size:15px}
  .kpis{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line);margin:34px 0 0}
  .kpi{background:var(--panel);padding:18px 18px 20px}
  .kpi .n{font-family:var(--display);font-weight:700;font-size:26px;color:#fff}
  .kpi .n span{color:var(--cobalt)}
  .kpi .l{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--faint);margin-top:6px;line-height:1.5}

  .sec{margin-top:56px}
  .sec h2{font-size:26px;margin-bottom:6px}
  .sec .lead{color:var(--muted);max-width:64ch;font-size:14px;margin-bottom:20px}

  /* moat / why us */
  .moat{border:1px solid var(--cobalt);background:rgba(31,59,255,.05);padding:24px 26px;margin-top:8px}
  .moat h3{font-size:20px;color:#fff;margin-bottom:8px}
  .moat p{color:var(--text);font-size:14px;max-width:70ch}
  .moat .hl{color:var(--green);font-weight:600}

  /* competitor table */
  table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;margin-top:6px;font-size:12.5px}
  th,td{text-align:left;padding:11px 12px;border:1px solid var(--line);vertical-align:top}
  thead th{background:var(--panel);font-family:var(--mono);font-size:9.5px;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--muted)}
  td.brand{font-weight:600;color:#fff;white-space:nowrap}
  .yes{color:var(--green);font-weight:700} .no{color:var(--faint)}
  tr.us td{background:rgba(31,59,255,.08)}
  tr.us td.brand{color:var(--cobalt)}
  .price-col{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:11px;color:var(--text)}

  /* why grid */
  .why3{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line)}
  .whyc{background:var(--panel);padding:18px 18px 20px}
  .whyc .k{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--green)}
  .whyc h3{font-size:15px;margin:8px 0 6px}
  .whyc p{font-size:12.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.5}

  /* growth engine flywheel */
  .engine{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(5,1fr);gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line);margin-top:6px}
  .node{background:var(--panel);padding:16px 15px 18px}
  .node .step{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10px;color:var(--cobalt);letter-spacing:.1em}
  .node h4{font-family:var(--display);font-size:15px;color:#fff;margin:7px 0 5px}
  .node p{font-size:11.5px;color:var(--muted);line-height:1.5}
  .cadence{margin-top:1px;border:1px solid var(--line);border-top:none;background:var(--panel);padding:14px 16px}
  .cadence .mono{color:var(--faint);margin-bottom:8px;display:block}
  .cadence table{margin-top:0;border:none}
  .cadence td,.cadence th{border:none;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);padding:7px 10px}
  .cadence th{background:transparent}

  /* offer / terms */
  .offer{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1.2fr 1fr;gap:1px;background:var(--line);border:1px solid var(--line);margin-top:8px}
  .offer .side{background:var(--panel);padding:24px 26px}
  .offer h3{font-size:19px;margin-bottom:12px}
  .termline{display:flex;justify-content:space-between;gap:12px;padding:10px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--line);font-size:13px}
  .termline:last-child{border-bottom:none}
  .termline .k{color:var(--muted)} .termline .v{color:#fff;font-weight:600;text-align:right}
  .cta{display:block;text-align:center;background:var(--cobalt);color:#fff;font-family:var(--mono);font-size:12px;letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;padding:15px;margin-top:18px;transition:.15s}
  .cta:hover{opacity:.9}
  .gated{font-family:var(--mono);font-size:10.5px;color:var(--faint);margin-top:12px;line-height:1.6}
  @media(max-width:820px){.kpis,.why3,.engine{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr}.offer{grid-template-columns:1fr}.hero h1{font-size:30px}}

</style>
</BaseLayout>
